description.narrative: High coverage of community-based nutrition and vaccination services was maintained at 84% and 87% respectively in municipalities for which data is available, after near doubling of coverage in 2018. Three additional municipalities in Maguindanao Province were declared open defecation free, making 10 municipalities OD-free to date, out of the 118 total municipalities and two cities in the Autonomous Region. Basic capacities and government commitments are now in place to expand nutrition, immunization and sanitation programming on a wider scale in 2020. Progress was constrained by the outbreak of polio and Mindanao earthquakes in the second half of the year. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:07/02/2020
